No. 172. Street-fighting.

Michael Ferrich, a journeyman shoemaker from Wiirzburg‚ came to blows with James Schmidt of Meilen about the month and eating flesh. The one said, ‘People eat flesh in March.² ‘No, that they don’t,' replied the other. ‘Well,' continued the stranger‚ ‘it seems to me there are folks in this country who can get on better with whey and cheese than with Scrip- ture.' And when he went on to chaff his fellow about his ‘old cow-country⁷ and so forth, they fell to settle it with their fists, till the neighbours made peace.
